JOHANNESBURG - The Gupta family says its business as usual, despite allegations their bank accounts are being shut down by the Bank of Baroda.Media reports claim the Mumbai-based bank was winding down its relationship with Gupta-linked companies.But the lawyer representing the family says this simply isn't true.Last year, South Africa s big four banks closed Gupta bank accounts, claiming to be following international banking regulations.The controversial family has a close relationship with President Jacob Zuma.They've been accused of trying to influence government decisions and National Treasury.eNCA